Qdrift: The main function¶

The following function calcualtes the drift, algorithms estimate of distribution, dynamic window size¶

In [8]:
# The following function calcualtes the drift, algorithms estimate of distribution, dynamic window size

def qdrift(series,delta):
    # Delta's standard of 0.01 , but Adwin builder can receive a floating point as the delta parameter.
    adwin = Adwin.Adwin(delta)
    f = open('output.txt','w')
    f.write('Length of series = ' + str(len(series)) + '\n')
    drift = []
    estimate = []
    width = [] 
    for data in series:
#         f.write(str(data))
#         print data
        if (adwin.update(data)):
            with open('output.txt', 'a') as f:
#                 print ("Change has been detected in data: "+str(data)+ 
#                         'at position'+ 
#                         str(series[series==data].index[0]) + '\n')
#                 time.sleep(1)
                f.write("Change has been detected in data: "+str(data)+ 
                        ' at position '+ 
                        str(series[series==data].index[0]) + '\n')
                drift.append(data)
                estimate.append(adwin.getEstimation())
                width.append(adwin.length()) 
                pass
        drift.append(0)
        estimate.append(adwin.getEstimation())
        width.append(adwin.length())
    if sum(drift) == 0:
        f.write("No drift detected")
    return drift,estimate,width

Series Plotter¶

In [4]:
# Plotting function
def fig(series,title,xlabel,ylabel):
    plt.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = [12, 8]
    plt.plot(series)
#     p.set_xlabel(str(xlabel))
#     p.set_ylabel(str(ylabel))
#     p.set_title(str(title))
    plt.xlabel(str(xlabel), fontsize = 10)
    plt.ylabel(str(ylabel), fontsize = 10)
    plt.title(str(title), fontsize = 20)
    return None

Example 2 : Synthetic Triangular Series¶

In [40]:
# Generate series
triangle = np.array([])
for i in range(1,10):
    y = np.linspace(0,200,100)
    y1 = np.linspace(200,0,100)
    triangle = np.append(triangle,np.append(y,y1))
# triangle = triangle.astype(int)
triangle = pd.Series(triangle)

# Generate series
scaled = np.array([])
for i in range(1,10):
    y = np.ones(50)
    y1 = np.append(y,np.ones(50)*5)
    y2 = np.append(y1,np.ones(50)*10)
    y3 = np.append(y2,np.ones(50)*15)    
    scaled = np.append(scaled,y3)
